data.title: A Plan of the City of Dresden Capital of Saxony by Scots Magazine: (1759) Map
data.meta_description: No Binding - Scots Magazine, |Edinburgh - 1759 - Condition: Good - Original C18th engraved map bound in "The Scots Magazine August 1759". Slightly browned. Page 437 "References to the plan of Dresden" landmarks include "New Town - Mione Street, The Lions, Barracks. Old Town - Wilsch Gate, Pilcher Gate, Playhouse, St Sophie, Pirna Gate, Seeberg, Count Bruhl's house" etc. Also included plate with "A plan of the battle of Minden". Booklet Size (approx.) 20.5 x 12.5 cm. - A Plan of the City of Dresden Capital of Saxony
